==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: lacebark
<hw>lacebark</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small tree or shrub (<spn>Hoheria
populnea</spn>) of New Zealand having a profusion of axillary clusters
of honey-scented paper-white flowers and whose bark is used for
cordage.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ribbonwood, houhere, <spn>Hoheria
populnea</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lace-bark</ent>⟦br⟧
